(40, 23, 15, 48, 6, 12, 12, NULL, 'Hypocrisy in Religious Practice', 'Both passages emphasize the hypocrisy of religious leaders who prioritize outward appearances over genuine faith. In Matthew, the scribes and Pharisees make proselytes who are worse off, while in Galatians, there is a concern about those who seek to impose circumcision for appearances'' sake.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
